From 47450490f74481a3979c6ddc289965cf2c601454 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 09:55:52 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 9.5 Session A: register the workbench Comments view
 ourselves
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Upstream's Comments view (the panel listing all comment threads on
all files) is registered by MainThreadComments only when an extension
declares the 'comments' contribution. KRT routes review comments
through KrtPrCommentController directly, with no extension in the
loop, so the view never showed up — the user couldn't browse threads
via the panel.

Add a KRT contribution that registers the same ViewContainer + View
descriptors at boot. hideIfEmpty: true keeps it hidden until the
controller pushes its first batch of comments via updateComments.
---
 .../pr/krtCommentsView.contribution.ts        | 65 +++++++++++++++++++
 .../pr/krtPullRequestEditor.contribution.ts   |  1 +
 2 files changed, 66 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtCommentsView.contribution.ts

diff --git a/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtCommentsView.contribution.ts b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtCommentsView.contribution.ts
new file mode 100644
index 00000000000..53b3ab91098
--- /dev/null
+++ b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtCommentsView.contribution.ts
@@ -0,0 +1,65 @@
+/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
